# Step-by-Step Implementation

## 1. Created an S3 Bucket

Created an S3 bucket for permission testing.

Bucket Name:
- sugandha-test-bucket

Purpose:
- To test bucket access using different IAM users.

---

## 2. Created Custom S3 Access Policy

Created a custom IAM policy for bucket access.

Policy Name:
- TestBucketAccess

Permissions Included:
- s3:ListBucket
- s3:GetObject
- s3:PutObject

Purpose:
- To provide bucket access to selected users.

---

## 3. Attached Allow Policy to Selected Users

The allow policy was attached to:

Allowed Users:
- Alpha
- s3-user

These users were allowed to:
- Open the S3 bucket
- Upload files
- View bucket contents
- Access bucket using direct URL

---

# Bucket Access Verification

Tested bucket access using:
- IAM login URL
- Incognito browser mode
- Separate IAM credentials

Verified that:
- Alpha user could access the bucket.
- s3-user could access the bucket successfully.

---

# Direct Bucket URL Testing

Used direct S3 bucket URL:

https://us-east-1.console.aws.amazon.com/s3/buckets/sugandha-test-bucket

Purpose:
- To test bucket access permissions directly.

Observation:
- Users with bucket permissions could open the bucket successfully.

---

# Blocking Restricted Users

## 4. Created Explicit Deny Policy

Created a deny policy to restrict bucket access for selected IAM users.

Policy Name:
- DenyTestBucketAccess

Blocked Permissions:
- s3:ListBucket
- s3:GetObject
- s3:PutObject

Purpose:
- To prevent unauthorized users from accessing the S3 bucket.

---

## 5. Attached Deny Policy to Restricted Users

The deny policy was attached to:

Blocked Users:
- admin-user
- developer-user
- billing-user

These users were restricted from:
- Viewing bucket contents
- Uploading files
- Opening the bucket
- Accessing bucket objects

---

# Access Restriction Testing

Logged in using blocked IAM users and tested S3 bucket access.

Observed Results:
- Access Denied
- Insufficient Permissions

Blocked users could not:
- Open bucket objects
- Upload files
- View bucket contents

